19
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:59,760
Now to really understand our suspect,

20
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,600
You gotta look at its background, right?

21
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,160
So most verbs have these three main forms.

22
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:07,920
You've got the present, like break, then
the simple past, broke,

23
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:11,320
and then there's this third form, the past
participle,

24
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:14,460
broken, and that's the one we're zeroing
in on.

25
00:01:14,460 --> 00:01:17,360
Okay, so here's the absolute crucial
point.

26
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:21,280
A past participle, it has what we call a
passive meaning.

27
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:24,240
This means it's not describing the noun
doing an action.

28
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:27,320
Nope, it's describing an action that was
done to it.

29
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:31,060
So, you know, the toy didn't break
something, It was broken.

30
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:35,940
See the difference? Okay, time to check
out our first big clue.

31
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:37,660
This is gonna show us what happens

32
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:41,140
when our past participle is what I like to
call a lone wolf

33
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:44,700
when it's working completely by itself.
And you know what?

34
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:47,140
The rule is so simple, it's great.

35
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:50,140
When the past participle is just that one
single word,

36
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,740
it acts exactly like a regular adjective.

37
00:01:52,740 --> 00:01:57,220
You know, like a red car or a big house.
It just pops right in there

38
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:59,340
before the noun it's describing.

39
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:03,300
And once you see it, you'll see this
pattern absolutely everywhere.

40
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:08,740
A broken toy, a used car, stolen money, a
boiled egg, see?

41
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:12,660
When that participle is flying solo, it
always comes first.

42
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:16,160
It's simple. It's clean. It's super
consistent.

43
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:19,020
