54
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,640
Now, if we tried to use rule number one,

55
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:06,320
we'd say something like a written in
English book.

56
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:09,000
And that just sounds wrong, doesn't it?

57
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,640
That's because the whole group, the whole
gang, has to stick together.

58
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:15,560
So, that brings us to a rule number two.

59
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:18,720
And this one is just as important as the
first.

60
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:21,520
The entire descriptive phrase, that's the
participle

61
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:24,120
and all its buddies, it has to stick
together

62
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:27,400
and it has to come after the noun it's
describing.

63
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,800
and you see this pattern playing out
consistently.

64
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,120
We don't say a made in Germany car, do we?

65
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:35,840
No, we say a car made in Germany. It's not
the cooked by Helen meal,

66
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:39,200
it's the meal cooked by Helen. The gang
always, always follows.

67
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,920
So there you have it. With just those two
simple rules,

68
